-- Bharti to Invest $600 Million in Its Nigerian Operations Over Three Years
-- Vincent Nwanma
-- 2010-07-06T12:47:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/bharti-to-invest-600-million-in-its-nigerian-operations-over-three-years.html

          
          
             Bharti Airtel Ltd., the Indian
mobile-phone company that last month completed a $9 billion
acquisition of Zain’s African assets, plans to invest $600
million in Nigeria over the next three years.  
 Half of that amount will be spent in the first year, Manoj
Kohli, chief executive officer of Bharti’s African unit, told
reporters today in Lagos, the commercial capital.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        